        "content": "Minor Electrical Repairs ($150-$400): Single outlet replacement, single switch replacement, GFCI outlet installation, light fixture replacement, simple circuit breaker replacement, doorbell repair, smoke detector installation or replacement, and minor wiring repairs in accessible locations. These straightforward repairs typically take 30-90 minutes and use readily available parts. | Moderate Electrical Repairs ($400-$1,200): Multiple outlet/switch replacements, dedicated circuit installation for appliances, subpanel repairs, multiple breaker replacements, bathroom/kitchen electrical upgrades to code, outdoor lighting installation, and [link:/services/outdoor-motion-lighting-tucson|motion sensor lighting systems]. These repairs require 2-4 hours and may involve running new wiring or installing specialized components. | Major Electrical Repairs ($1,200-$3,500): Partial rewiring (single room or circuit), electrical service mast repair, meter base replacement, multiple dedicated circuits, whole-house surge protection, generator connection preparation, and extensive troubleshooting for intermittent problems. Major repairs involve 4-8 hours of skilled labor and significant materials. | Whole-House Electrical Projects ($3,500-$12,000+): Complete [link:/services/electrical-panel-upgrades-tucson|electrical panel replacement] (100A to 200A service upgrade), whole-house rewiring, main service upgrade from utility connection, aluminum wiring remediation, and knob-and-tube wiring replacement. These comprehensive projects require 1-5 days depending on home size and may involve permit fees, utility coordination, and inspection requirements."
